<p>
  <span class="nym">Serlo</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Old English</span> <i>searo</i>, <span class="lang">Old High German</span> <i>saro</i> 'device, contrivance; armour, war equipment'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>The English form <i>Serl</i> is witnessed in 1379 in the relational byname <i>Serlsoñ</i> (<span class="bibl"><span class="key">WRYPT1</span> <span class="loc">p. 320</span></span>).</p>
  
  


